issue.title: Fix bugs
issue.body:
Changes:
- make stages public so they can be used independently of the main fuzzer
- return Some(None) instead of just None when generating an Option since returning None by itself would mean generation failed.
- directly add types to ty_map if they're not present yet as otherwise empty structs aren't registered since they have no members that can register them.
- don't call v.generate for struct generation. Because:
    1. This will always fail for empty structs so they won't be generated at all
    2. This doesn't really make sense for structs as this will just tell us if some random member is recursive but we will generate all of them anyways. Also I'd argue that you can only recurse though enums so this should always be false.

issue.title: glTF coordinate conversion issues related to node conversion

labels.name: S-Needs-Triage
labels.description: This issue needs to be labelled

issue.body:
## Bevy version and features

bf4f0e5e1dd4dd7712c9c404cf40715d09abbdc7

## Background

The [glTF coordinate conversion](https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/pull/19633) assumes that nodes within the scene are following glTF scene semantics (+Z forward) and should be converted to Bevy semantics (-Z forward).

To make things more fun, glTF cameras and lights have different semantics - the conversion has to apply a special case correction:
https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/blob/d07a20a993015fef67e9376bfbe946c86a091011/crates/bevy_gltf/src/loader/gltf_ext/scene.rs#L48-L52

## Problems

1. Animated camera and light transforms are broken.
    - The special case is not applied to animation tracks, so animated cameras and lights face the wrong direction.
    - This is likely to affect some users.
2. Child nodes of cameras and lights are broken.
    - The special case is inherited by child nodes, so non-camera/light child nodes face the wrong direction.
        - (This is a bit speculative - I haven't tested it)
    - Is this a niche case? Maybe relevant for a first person game that wants to attach a mesh to the camera?
3. A node can't be both a mesh and a camera and/or light.
    - Meshes are converted differently from cameras/lights, and Bevy can't represent this.
    - Probably extremely niche to non-existent in practice - most DCCs and engines (inc. Godot and Unreal) can't represent this either.
4. Scene conversion depends on node+mesh conversion.
    - Some users may want the scene as a whole to be converted, but without touching node transforms and mesh assets.
    - Hard to tell how many users would want this. Unreal only supports node conversion.

## Solutions

1 and 2 are probably fixable. Needs more logic for special cases and tracking parent transforms.

3 can be worked around, e.g. by splitting the node into separate entities. But it's probably such a niche case that the complexity isn't worth it - better to report an error.

4 is fixable by applying a correction to the scene root entity instead of nodes. The user would have to choose which conversion they prefer.

PR #20394 technically fixes all these issues, but at the cost of removing node conversion entirely. It's unclear how many users would consider this a problem.

There's also the "forward flag" proposal (https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/pull/20135) - this may fix all or some of these issues, but the details haven't been worked out.

pull_request.title: some minor improvements
pull_request.body:
This pull request introduces several improvements and new features to the codebase, focusing on enhancing the voting experience on questions and replies, improving developer experience with new seeders and factories, updating environment configuration, and adding new styling. The most significant changes include the addition of AJAX support for voting, the creation of database seeders and factories for easier testing and development, and updates to environment and documentation files.

**Voting System Enhancements**
* Added AJAX support to upvote/downvote methods in both `QuestionController` and `ReplyController`, allowing for real-time updates and the ability to remove votes (toggle upvote/downvote), with clear user feedback messages. Also, now tracks the user's vote status for questions and replies. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-6c4cca9be8aad3767012d6cae332e96c81e086135267068b8093914683306f41L74-R92) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-6c4cca9be8aad3767012d6cae332e96c81e086135267068b8093914683306f41L86-R138) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-6c4cca9be8aad3767012d6cae332e96c81e086135267068b8093914683306f41L113-R184) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-44c580f97a556bbc32180844fd34a6d51d0708cec590a8d3f34a060d0c04f38fL48-R82) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-44c580f97a556bbc32180844fd34a6d51d0708cec590a8d3f34a060d0c04f38fL73-R128)
* Reduced the number of most used tags displayed on the question index page from 10 to 5 for better UI clarity.

**Database and Seeding Improvements**
* Added new model factories for `Question`, `Reply`, and `Vote` to simplify the creation of test data. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-f23a86e736f1e9ed0eb300ed668d158f247eac81f8aa5ffa1a416c3a50bc38caR1-R26) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-d847605951895b0c2e1ae8b1c1446fe0e4a7fac20ca8660d7332af8f8d21c357R1-R23) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-b06c3cb859e1441f0d548c7cc1d7e27019a56896b86d488d54ad327011c26ee6R1-R23)
* Introduced a comprehensive `DummyDataSeeder` for populating the database with sample users, questions, and replies, and updated `DatabaseSeeder` to use it. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-c3757c27404c304baef34c2e2bacd21e7eb3beba8af5e1373d193c187c993e89R1-R89) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-ccad8b4ee6013765c2bc672aa0515f8e99e42949c914cce01e0cb2b4e882775dL16-R16)

**Styling and UI**
* Added a new `resources/css/index.css` file with Tailwind-based and custom styles for improved UI consistency and dark mode support.
* Minor cleanup in `login.css` by removing an unused Google Fonts import.

**Configuration and Documentation Updates**
* Updated `.env.example` to use MySQL instead of SQLite and switched mail settings to use Gmail SMTP for a more realistic development environment. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-a3046da0d15a27e89f2afe639b25748a7ad4d9290af3e7b1b6c1a5533c8f0a8cL22-R27) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-a3046da0d15a27e89f2afe639b25748a7ad4d9290af3e7b1b6c1a5533c8f0a8cL49-R55)
* Improved project setup instructions in `README.md`, including running the queue worker and formatting steps as a numbered list.
* Added the `mallardduck/blade-lucide-icons` package to `composer.json` for icon support.
